{"id":14881912,"mediaExerciseId":"0ac846fb-487b-44e6-bdc7-11f8b28dd1db","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"25","chapterTitle":"Option Valuation","groupId":612507,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":855,"solutions":[{"id":5995417,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"The strategy of holding the asset and a put option to avoid the downside risk is called a protective put.\n\nThe protective put is considered as stock insurance because it provides safety against losses when the corresponding asses decline its value. Also, it limits the losses to the premium paid to acquire the put option. This is because the maximum an investor can face the loss is equal to the\npremium paid.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/169ccd108cf8f8bb0363a91c8111c655/5fe52cbb761dd59cac29995e3e2e8536/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/169ccd108cf8f8bb0363a91c8111c655/5fe52cbb761dd59cac29995e3e2e8536/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Since by buying a protective put, there is an assurance that the investor can either get the market value of the stock or the strike price of the option. \n\nTherefore, a protective put is also considered\nas stock insurance.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/169ccd108cf8f8bb0363a91c8111c655/aac86317c8c886c52ef98fef8ea9992e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/169ccd108cf8f8bb0363a91c8111c655/aac86317c8c886c52ef98fef8ea9992e/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid"